job_history.work_description: Analyze requirements and produce solutions in accordance with best practices in employment and human resource law as it relates to independent consultants, contractors, and temporary labor. Architect solutions that exceed program objectives through in-depth analysis of business requirements. Facilitate discovery of business information and processes to uncover potential areas of risk. Selected to lead the management of program implementation including project initiation, planning, execution and closure.

Manage programs to ensure account satisfaction and operational delivery of defined objectives. Develop effective relationships with key stakeholder involved in client programs. Screen and hire senior level professionals as well as coordinate orientations. Actively train, mentor, and consult new employees hired by the company.

Educate and communicate regarding complex human resource, legal, financial, and system transactions. Administration of benefits including retirement, profit sharing, medical, dental, life, and disability insurance. Oversee invoicing, payroll, expense processing and reconciliation for assigned accounts.

Proactively initiate, develop, and manage long-term, profitable relationships. Manage existing client relationships to identify future needs and consultatively address them. Profile prospects and clients to indentify additional financial needs, and refer to appropriate financial partners.

Analyze requirements and produce solutions in accordance with best practices in employment and human resource law as it relates to independent consultants, contractors, and temporary labor. Architect solutions that exceed program objectives through in-depth analysis of business requirements.

skills.name: Human Resource Management
skills.explanation: Has extensive experience in human resource management, including education and work experience in the field, indicating expert-level mastery.

skills.name: Project Management
skills.explanation: Has experience managing programs and projects, including project initiation, planning, execution, and closure, showing strong proficiency.

skills.name: Leadership
skills.explanation: Has experience leading teams and managing programs, including training, mentoring, and consulting new employees, indicating strong proficiency.

skills.name: Communication
skills.explanation: Has experience communicating complex information to various stakeholders, including employees, clients, and management, showing strong proficiency.

skills.name: Business Analysis
skills.explanation: Has experience analyzing business requirements and producing solutions, including in-depth analysis of business processes, indicating strong proficiency.

skills.name: Risk Management
skills.explanation: Has experience identifying potential areas of risk and facilitating discovery of business information and processes, showing solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Payroll Management
skills.explanation: Has experience overseeing payroll processing and reconciliation, showing solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Benefits Administration
skills.explanation: Has experience administering benefits, including retirement, profit sharing, medical, dental, life, and disability insurance, showing solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Financial Management
skills.explanation: Has some experience with financial transactions, including invoicing and expense processing, but lacks extensive experience, indicating some practical experience.
